result.execSummary:
The defendant Alexander Taylor Livingston was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Vehicle Operator Flee/Elude Officer, a class I felony, Wisconsin Statutes 346.04(3).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

miscConds.notes:
Pay $100.00 fine plus costs.   Payment is due within 30 days.  If the Defendant cannot make the payment, he/she must report to the Clerk of Courts Office to set up a payment plan.  Failure to comply will result in other collection methods including a civil Judgment and/or suspension of your drivers license for two (2) years.  This judgment may be collected by income assignment if you fail to pay fines and costs as ordered.
-------------------------------
Provide biological specimen to state crime lab for DNA analysis, and pay DNA analysis surcharge.

IT IS HEREBY ORDERED THAT the defendant's excess work release funds be applied to any & all outstanding Court obligations while serving his mandatory jail sentence.
-------------------------------

No alcohol.   No illegal drugs or drug paraphernalia. Any prescription medications to be made known to Agent and taken as prescribed.   Not to operate a motor vehicle without a valid driver's license.
-------------------------------

Counseling as recommended by Probation Agent.   The defendant must pay Department of Corrections Supervision fees.
-------------------------------

AODA assessment and follow through with recommendations.
-------------------------------

timeConds.notes: with work release privileges to commence on or before 06/06/2016 at 8:00 a.m. May travel to Illinois for employment purposes. **Sixty (60) days STAYED for Agent's use.
